[{:rule-id "rule-ai", :item {:feed-id "hn-frontpage", :item-id "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47826104", :title "Show HN: Faceoff – A terminal UI for following NHL games", :link "https://www.vincentgregoire.com/faceoff/", :published-at #inst "2026-04-19T17:44:44.000-00:00", :content "Faceoff is a TUI app written in Python to follow live NHL games and browse standings and stats. I got the inspiration from Playball, a similar TUI app for MLB games that was featured on HN. The app was mostly vibe-coded with Claude Code, but not one-shot. I added features and fixed bugs by using it, as I spent way too much time in the terminal over the last few months. Try it out with `uvx faceoff` (requires uv). Comments URL: https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47826104 Points: 11 # Comments: 2"}, :excerpts [{:text "... on HN. The app was mostly vibe-coded with Claude Code, but not one-shot. I added features and...", :matched-terms ["claude"], :source :content}]}]